canonical:
  title: 九成宮懷古
  author: 朴仁範
  language: lzh
  text: 憶昔文皇定鼎年四方無事幸林泉歌鍾響徹煙霄外羽衛光分草樹前玉榭金階靑靄合翠樓丹檻白雲連追思冠劒橋山月千古行人盡慘然
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 九成宮懷古
  author: 朴仁範
  language: lzh
  text: 憶昔文皇定鼎年。四方無事幸林泉。歌鍾響徹煙霄外。羽衛光分草樹前。玉榭金階靑靄合。翠樓丹檻白雲連。追思冠劒橋山月。千古行人盡慘然。
korean:
  title: 구성궁 회고
  author: 박인범
  language: kor
  text: |-
    옛날 문황께서 천하를 통일한 때에
    사방이 무사하여 임천에 노니셨더니
    노래와 쇠북소리 중천에 멀리 사무쳤고
    우림군 호위병들이 나무 앞에 줄지었었지
    옥 누각 금 섬돌엔 푸른 안개 어울리고
    푸른 다락 붉은 난간엔 흰 구름이 잇따랐지
    관과 검을 버리신 교산 달을 생각하니
    천고의 지나는 사람 모두 눈물짓누나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0150_010_0290&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 구성궁(九成宮) : '
    value: 수(隋)나라의 인수궁(仁壽宮)으로 피서(避暑)궁이었으며, 당태종(唐太宗)이 그 궁을 수리하여 피서할 때 이름을 고쳐 구성이라 하였다 한다.
  - key: '[주-D002] 교산(橋山) : '
    value: 황제의 능(陵)인데, 여기서는 태종이 관검(冠劒)을 버리고 죽은 곳을 말한다.
english:
  title: Reflections on the Palace of Nine Perfections
  author: Park In-beom
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I recall when the Emperor of Wen unified all beneath heaven—
    The four quarters lay peaceful, blessed in garden and stream.
    Songs and bells rang out, their echoes piercing the clouds,
    While the imperial guard stood arrayed like sentinels before the trees.
    Jade pavilions and golden steps merged with azure mist,
    Emerald towers and vermillion railings touched by white clouds.
    Yet thinking of him who laid down his crown and sword at Bridgemont,
    All travelers through the ages weep in sorrow.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The Palace of Nine Perfections was originally the Renshou Palace of the Sui Dynasty, built as a summer retreat. Emperor Taizong of Tang restored and renamed it.
  - key: ''
    value: Bridgemont (Qiaoshan) refers to the mausoleum of emperors, here representing the place where Emperor Taizong was finally laid to rest, his regalia surrendered.
